issue.description:
Build Identifier: 20090920-1017

Description looks like https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=239155 but I believe this is separate issue.

We have our product based on JSDT. Our Explorer did not always show newly created projects. I haven't seen this problem with WTP projects in "clean" WTP install.

Basically, the problem seems to be that the root of the explorer view is IWorkspaceRoot, not IWorkspace. org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.internal.ui.navigator.JavaNavigatorContentProvider#314 should add getRoot() when modifying the parent to pass to super.

In our code we had to do:
		if (parent instanceof IJavaScriptModel)
			super.postAdd(((IJavaScriptModel) parent).getWorkspace(), element, runnables);
		else if (parent instanceof IJavaScriptProject) 
			super.postAdd( ((IJavaScriptProject)parent).getProject(), element, runnables);
		else
			super.postAdd(parent, element, runnables);


