As far as I know Riena ImageStore supports only unique names of icons / images.
But in reality it can happen that the same name of an Icon is located in different sizes at different pathes.

per ex. if following the naming schema 
http://standards.freedesktop.org/icon-naming-spec/icon-naming-spec-latest.html
this can happen:

/icons/16x16/apps/office-calendar.png
/icons/32x32/apps/office-calendar.png

at the moment I have to rename / relocate like this:

/icons/office-calendar-16x16.png
/icons/office-calendar-32x32.png

but it would be better to register the path 
icons
at extension ImagePaths

and use as icon names
16x16/apps/office-calendar.png
32x32/apps/office-calendar.png

if we change the first part of getImageDescriptor(String fullName) as follows,
this would be possible.

