Subversive always use the first line of the property bugtraq:logregex to validate the issue number in the commit dialog. According:
http://tortoisesvn.net/docs/release/TortoiseSVN_en/tsvn-dug-bugtracker.html
Subversive should use the second line of bugtraq:logregex when there is two lines into that property.

In the source file:
src/org/eclipse/team/svn/ui/composite/CommentComposite.java
near line 190, the bugtraq:logregex property is used in a wrong manner:

this.validationManager.attachTo(this.bugIdText, new AbstractVerifier() {
  protected String getErrorMessage(Control input) {
    String logregex = CommentComposite.this.bugtraqModel.isNumber() ?
              "[0-9]+(,?[0-9]+)*" //$NON-NLS-1$
             : ((CommentComposite.this.bugtraqModel.getLogregex() != null) ?
                 CommentComposite.this.bugtraqModel.getLogregex()[0] : null);
    if (logregex != null) {
      String bugId = this.getText(input);
      if (bugId.length() > 0 && !bugId.matches(logregex)) {
        ...cut...
        return SVNUIMessages.format(
                   SVNUIMessages.CommentComposite_BugID_Verifier_Error_Text,
                   new String[] {
                       CommentComposite.this.bugtraqModel.getLabel(),
                       CommentComposite.this.bugtraqModel.getLogregex()[0] }
                   );
		}
	}
	return null;
}


CommentComposite.this.bugtraqModel.getLogregex()[1] should be used instead of CommentComposite.this.bugtraqModel.getLogregex()[0] when it exist.

